This paper discusses fairness in algorithmic classification, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves discussions of probability and risk assessment, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on fairness and trade-offs could also place it in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
